Package com.cafean.document.notebook

Class AbstractNotebookExporter

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.cafean.document.notebook.AbstractNotebookExporter
  • public abstract class AbstractNotebookExporter
extends java.lang.Object
    This class writes the contents of a model as an ExportableTextDocument implementation. This is the abstract implementation of the model notebook exporter that must be extended by individual plug-ins.

      • exportCollapsedRealTable

        public void exportCollapsedRealTable​(ComponentElement target,
                                     java.lang.String tableName,
                                     java.lang.String indexTitle,
                                     java.lang.String columnPrefix,
                                     CReal[][] values,
                                     java.lang.Class unitClass)
        Exports the given 2D array of values as a collapsed table. This method automatically collapses columns which are equivalent across all rows into ranges, then all rows which are equivalent into ranges. Row indexes are automatically created as the first column; column indexes are automatically created in the table header.

        This method will not create column spans for ranges where some other row or column does not equivalently span. Thus, the table

        Edge Data
        444
        556
        will be compressed to (including column indexes)
        Edge Data
        1-23
        44
        56

        Column headers are created in the following form: columnPrefix <range> where <range> may be a single index or a range of indexes. If the original data only has one column, then no range or index is applied at all.

        If the table has 0 elements (values.length is 0 or values[0].length is 0), the method returns immediately.

        Parameters:
        target - the ComponentElement to export tables for
        tableName - the name of the new table
        indexTitle - the name of the index column
        columnPrefix - the prefix applied to the ranges in column headers
        values - the values the form the basis of the table
        unitClass -
        Throws:
        java.lang.NullPointerException - if any value in the range values[0 to values.length-1][0 to values[0].length-1] is null
        java.lang.ArrayIndexOutOfBoundsException - if any row in values has a length less than values[0].length

      • createCollapsableRowTable

        public com.apt.doc.components.ExportableTable createCollapsableRowTable​(java.lang.Object target,
                                                                        java.lang.String tableName,
                                                                        java.lang.Object[] columnNames,
                                                                        int[] columnWidths)
        Creates a collapsable row table with standard styles. This table will create collapse equivalent ranges given the following conditions:
        1. The first element in each new row is an Integer. This element will be labelled the index element, and will be replaced when contiguous ranges of equivalent values are discovered.
        2. The index is monotonic with previous indexes.
        3. Index increments are no greater than 1.
        Parameters:
        target -
        tableName -
        columnNames -
        columnWidths -
        Returns:

      • plot

        public void plot​(double[] independentData,
                 double[]... dependentData)

        dependentData - the dependent data plotted along the graph's Y axis

        public void exportViewImage​(ViewComponent view)
                     throws java.io.IOException
        Exports a ViewComponent display as an image in the document. This method will open views that are not displayed, a necessary step in painting them to an image buffer. Any views opened by this method will be closed before its completion.

      • writeCollapsedSameValueColumns

        public void writeCollapsedSameValueColumns​(boolean firstColumnDisplay,
                                           java.lang.Object target,
                                           com.apt.doc.components.ExportableTable table)
        Export routine which will collapse columns of same data and place those values in a summary table. The format of the table must be as follows: One header row First row being the independent variable column. One or more dependent variable columns
        Parameters:
        firstColumnDisplay - the boolean which determines if the first column in the table is used only for formatting the table. This prevents the case where a table is written with only one column, and that column contains useless data. (ie a single column of cell indexes)
        target - the AbstractComponent which owns the data for the table.
        table - the ExportableTable to collapse same values
